## Code Usage Policy for ANA600 and ANA605

The code provided in this course is protected under an Educational Use License.
You may use and modify the code **only** for completing your coursework in
ANA600 or ANA605.

### Course Repository
Course additional resources are available here:  
https://github.com/mcvanderbilt/nu-ana600-605-student-resources

### What you *can* do
- Use the code for assignments.
- Modify it as part of your work.
- Submit your modified version.

### What you *cannot* do
- Post the code or your modified version anywhere (GitHub, Chegg, StackOverflow, etc.).
- Share the code with anyone outside the course.
- Use AI tools (Copilot, ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude, etc.) to modify or generate code.
- Use the code after the course ends.

### If you modify the code
Include:
- “Modified from original code by Matthew C. Vanderbilt for ANA600/ANA605 coursework.”
- A short description of your changes.
- Your name and student ID.

Violations of this policy may result in academic integrity actions.

If you have questions about what is allowed, please ask before submitting work.
